item.title: Response
item.dc:creator: vlad
item.content:encoded:
Response - Short Documentary
Response is a 10-minute short documentary highlighting the work of two search and rescue organisations in Ireland; Drogheda River Rescue & Recovery and Waterford Marine Search & Rescue. The documentary focuses on the people in these organisations, as well as their work in suicide prevention within their local communities.I took the role of director and lead editor in the project, as well as contributing to graphic elements of the project additional filming of footage.
WINNER OF BEST 2ND YEAR GROUP PROJECT 2015
Institute of Technology Blanchardstown
The Second Year Group Project is a year-long project in the Creative Digital Media course, in which, over the course of the academic year, groups of 4 are tasked with completing a large project, in our case, a ten-minute short documentary. These projects can be video-based, website development and design, animation, or rebranding and graphic design.Our short documentary, Response, was awarded as joint-winner along with a short animation.
[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zSHm7gv9BFk&t=3s[/embed]

item.title: Live from Kaleidoscope
item.dc:creator: vlad
item.content:encoded:
RT Blue of the Night: Live from Kaleidoscope
This video for RT's Lyric FM was the first commission I had for the 'Blue of the Night' programme. Along with my collaboration partner, Brendan Corcoran, I directed and edited this short highlight video for the Kaleidoscope live event, which ran in June 2016. This was the first piece of commercial work I was involved in, which brought forward a new challenge for me as a filmmaker, as this video came with a lot less license for abstract creativity, compared to the music video work I had previously been commissioned for. This allowed my to hone my skills in this style of production and editing. We filmed various acts that performed throughout the event and put together a short highlight video for programme's online and social media platforms.
[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=77dqyCw2wuM[/embed]

item.title: Maria Greenan
item.dc:creator: vlad
item.content:encoded:
"Maria Greenan - I Put a Spell On You"
Music Video
This was the second music video I worked on, under the title of 'Able Frame', the production team, consisting of myself and colleague, Brendan Corcoran. After consultation with the artist, Maria Greenan and her producer Ben Rawlins, we directed this abstract piece based around a live performance.After seeing our first video, 'Dramamine', both Greenan and Rawlins had asked us to incorporate a similar style, i.e. keeping the video heavy in abstract visuals using stock and archive footage.
Although we could take our experience from the first video, we wanted to use this project as an opportunity to attempt to bridge the gap between the abstract nature of our previous video, as had been requested, while making the video slightly more approachable for a broader audience as we felt this fit the target audience better for this particular project.
[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=adwL8OP6zns[/embed]

item.title: Owensie
item.dc:creator: vlad
item.content:encoded:
Owensie - 'Dramamine' Music Video
The music video for 'Dramamine' by the Irish artist Owensie was the first music video I produced with my colleague and collaboration partner, Brendan Corcoran. We worked under the name 'Able Frame' for this project and various other projects afterward.
'Dramamine' was an experimental music video, I took the project as an opportunity to try out some new ideas and skills in order to advance my editing skills. I worked on all aspects of the project, from concept to the final cut. We used a mixture of stock images and footage and our own captured work to produce the abstract piece, which we had agreed upon with the artist.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u7WKNwHklW8
